<subSubSection id="9EC177ED6283940CEE03E6AB186FFE45" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="C1D37E42DE750C6C39B86247978F92BD" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC7E92FB0ACE594EE832E0495E1665DC" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The form and pattern of tegmental granules together with the three aesthete pores are most similar to the images of 
<taxonomicName id="4039CF9F3D6F156F3D8E741A42275950" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochiton macleani" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleani">Leptochiton macleani</taxonomicName>
(Sirenko, 2015: figs 34-36). Voucher NHM_446 length approx 10 mm, width 3.2 mm (Fig. 21).
</paragraph>
<caption id="42FBEBEADE8ED1E57DF5535A4F1C5179" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph id="6550C3F030F793511119809B3439E786" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 21. 
<taxonomicName id="AE1CF639343E8D21D2B22FA9DB73F837" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochiton macleani" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleani">Leptochiton macleani</taxonomicName>
Sirenko, 2015. NHM_446 voucher specimen. A Live specimen (lateral view) after recovery from the ROV scoop sample B Preserved specimen (ventro-lateral view) following DNA extraction C Dorsal view D surface detail E SEM of tegmentum surface and pores. Scale bars: 4 mm (A); 0.5 mm (D); 0.3 mm (E). Image attribution Glover, Taylor, Ikebe, Dahlgren &amp; Wiklund, 2017.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
